# Terra VI Frontend — environment variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in for your environment.
# .env.local is gitignored — never commit actual URLs.

# ── LOCAL DEVELOPMENT ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave VITE_API_URL empty. Vite's dev proxy routes /api → localhost:8000.
# VITE_API_URL=

# ── GITHUB CODESPACES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Start the backend: uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
# 2. In VS Code Ports panel → port 8000 → right-click → Port Visibility → Public
# 3. Copy the forwarded URL from the Ports panel (the "Forwarded Address" column)
#    It looks like: https://didactic-fortnight-76p7vqw746xcp6jg-8000.app.github.dev
# 4. Paste it here:
#
# VITE_API_URL=https://YOUR-CODESPACE-NAME-8000.app.github.dev
#
# 5. Restart the frontend: npm run dev
# Note: the backend allows all origins in development mode, so no CORS config needed.

# ── PRODUCTION ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-deployed-api.fly.dev
